Pre-Game Insights: Morocco are widely tipped as the tournament's strongest contenders before a ball was kicked.
The Atlas Lions initially lived up to expectations in their opening match, dispatching group minnows Tanzania by a convincing 3-0 margin.
However, their quest for a smooth run hit a snag in their second outing, a frustrating 1-1 draw against DR Congo.
South Africa huffed and puffed their way into the round of 16, finishing second in Group E with four points.
Bafana Bafana are familiar foes for Morocco, having played them twice during the qualifying series for this tournament, with both teams picking up one win each.
